cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE

This paper involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks to encode human gaze information and decode visual representations of search targets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves human-computer interaction and the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves the prediction of user intents, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of neural networks for encoding and decoding suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
